All described procedures have been tested and work equally well for hiPSCs and hESCs.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5gtuq","text":"Until otherwise indicated, feeder-free hPSCs are routinely grown in a humidified cell culture incubator under “low” oxygen conditions. steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"g43n","text":"Prepare one 6-well VTN/Matrigel/Geltrex-coated plate for each vial of frozen hPSCs. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aa6qo","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ad6su","text":"A detailed protocol on \"Coating plates\" can be found in the \"Feeder-free culturing of hPSCs\" collection. A link to this collection can be found in the title section of this protocol, located above","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1coqm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1dt8n","text":"Pipette thawed cell suspension into 10 ml pre-warmed DMEM/F12.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4520j","text":"Place vial of frozen hPSCs in    water bath with constant agitation. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":30,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"dm58i","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"7E5EC3907E1711ECB658DD7F633A54EA","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"37","unit":10}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dr0b0","text":"While cells are spinning, aspirate the VTN/Matrigel/Geltrex solution from the coated plates and add 2 ml pre-warmed Feeder-free medium + Rock inhibitor to each well. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2djav","text":"Aspirate most of the medium on the centrifuged hPSCs, being careful not to disturb the pellet","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cnfms","text":"Spread the cells by moving the plate in left-right, then backward-forward motion.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e2h4","text":"Check the cells under the microscope to get an idea of the resulting cell density.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"u77v","text":"Dispense the cells onto the VTN/Matrigel/Geltrex-coated plate, adding 160 µl per well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5npe5","text":"Change 2 ml pre-warmed Feeder-free medium for each well every other day. When large colonies emerge or hPSCs density reaches 50-80%, passage using Accutase or ReLeSR. It usually takes 5-7 days for the thawed cells to grow to this point. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9e25r","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4vbs4","text":"A detailed protocol on passaging using Accutase or ReLeSR can be found in the \"Passaging of hPSCs\" protocol, in the \"Feeder-free culturing of hPSCs\" collection. A link to this collection can be found in the title section of this protocol, located above","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"880st","text":"Place the plate in the low oxygen incubator","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
